<subSubSection id="C3246572FF84C92BFF62FE07FD63FD95" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF84C92BFF62FE07FD63FD95" blockId="37.[151,1437,258,1118]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFF62FE07FEB4FE64" bold="true" box="[199,314,397,423]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF84C92BFE16FE05FDCAFE6B" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[435,580,398,424]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carabobo" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFE16FE05FDCAFE6B" box="[435,580,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">M. carabobo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFDE9FE04FD31FE6B" bold="true" box="[588,703,398,424]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF84C92BFDE9FE04FD31FE6B" box="[588,703,398,424]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are distinguished from those of other congeners by the palp with embolus roughtly straight lacking any projections or membranous areas (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFC72FE3AFBF7FE08" box="[983,1145,432,459]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–132" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1779,1803]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,181,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-23@38.[156,1430,181,1755]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 126–132. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 126–129 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (126 prolateral, 127 ventral, 128 retrolateral, 129 detail of embolus); 130–132 Female (AMNH, paratype) (130 epigyne, 131 vulva; 132 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection of the cymbium; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP— spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550486/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 127, 129</figureCitation>
). Females resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF84C92BFF12FE5EFEB5FE2E" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[183,315,468,493]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arraijan" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFF12FE5EFEB5FE2E" box="[183,315,468,493]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">M. arraijan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFEE1FE59FE36FE2E" bold="true" box="[324,440,467,493]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF84C92BFEE1FE59FE36FE2E" box="[324,440,467,493]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFE6DFE59FDEBFE2E" box="[456,613,467,493]" captionStart="FIGURES 118–123" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1318,1342]" captionTargetBox="[156,1421,429,1284]" captionTargetId="figure-95@36.[155,1433,417,1294]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 118–123. 118–120 Meri aparia spec. nov., female (ex MNHN 2028, holotype) (118 epigyne, 119 vulva, 120 schematic course of internal duct system); 121–123 Meri arraijan spec. nov., female (AMNH, paratype) (121 epigyne, 122 vulva, 123 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD— fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; SP—spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550283/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 121–123</figureCitation>
) by the epigyne with EF bearing a long, transversal anterior groove and EP opening posteriorly on MS. They are distinguished from the latter species by the MS widest medially and EP with anterior margin surpassing half MS length (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFD65FD92FCAEFDF0" box="[704,800,536,563]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–132" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1779,1803]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,181,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-23@38.[156,1430,181,1755]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 126–132. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 126–129 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (126 prolateral, 127 ventral, 128 retrolateral, 129 detail of embolus); 130–132 Female (AMNH, paratype) (130 epigyne, 131 vulva; 132 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection of the cymbium; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP— spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550486/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 130</figureCitation>
) (MS widest anteriorly and EP with anterior margin not surpassing half MS length in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF84C92BFE45FDB6FDECFD96" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[480,610,572,597]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arraijan" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFE45FDB6FDECFD96" box="[480,610,572,597]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">M. arraijan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFDCFFDB1FD52FD96" bold="true" box="[618,732,571,597]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF84C92BFDCFFDB1FD52FD96" box="[618,732,571,597]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FF84C92BFF62FDD7FD4FFBF8" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF84C92BFF62FDD7FDC3FC8A" blockId="37.[151,1437,258,1118]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFF62FDD7FDA2FDB4" bold="true" box="[199,556,605,632]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF84C92BFE14FDD7FD91FDB4" box="[433,543,605,631]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 12.8. Prosoma: 5.7 long, 5.2 wide. Opisthosoma: 6.9 long, 4.2 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.45, 0.37, 0.25, 0.37; interdistances: 0.23, 0.10, 0.50, 0.50, 0.28, 0.20. Legs: I: 33.2 (9.0, 3.1, 9.0, 9.8, 2.3); II: 36.9 (10.0, 3.3, 10.4, 10.9, 2.3); III: 23.4 (6.2, 2.6, 6.5, 6.4, 1.7); IV: 27.9 (8.2, 2.5, 7.4, 7.9, 1.9). Spination follows the generic pattern except tibiae I–II: d1-0-1; metatarsus IV: r1-1-2. Palp: PTA triangular, as long as wide; RTA gutter-shaped, slightly widened distally and blunt, roughly 2 times longer than its widest part (retrolateral view); cymbium with small retro proximal projection; subtegulum barely visible between 11–12 o’clock in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFE94FCA4FE40FC8B" box="[305,462,814,840]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–132" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1779,1803]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,181,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-23@38.[156,1430,181,1755]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 126–132. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 126–129 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (126 prolateral, 127 ventral, 128 retrolateral, 129 detail of embolus); 130–132 Female (AMNH, paratype) (130 epigyne, 131 vulva; 132 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection of the cymbium; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP— spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550486/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 126–129</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFE7FFCA4FDCEFC8A" box="[474,576,814,841]" captionStart="FIGURES 133–137" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[260,1319,1226,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-521@39.[256,1332,1209,1940]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 133–137. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 133–135 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (133 prolateral, 134 ventral, 135 retrolateral); 136–137 Female (AMNH, paratype) (136 epigyne, 137 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550488/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">133–135</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF84C92BFF62FCDBFD4FFBF8" blockId="37.[151,1437,258,1118]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF84C92BFF62FCDBFE21FCA9" bold="true" box="[199,431,848,875]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF84C92BFE95FCDAFE2CFCA9" box="[304,418,848,874]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">paratype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 13.9. Prosoma 5.6 long, 5.8 wide. Opisthosoma 7.3 long, 4.5 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.40, 0.35, 0.30, 0.35; interdistances: 0.38, 0.25, 0.55, 0.62, 0.36, 0.25. Legs: I: 24.3 (7.0, 3.0, 6.2, 6.4, 1.7); II: - (7.5, 3.0, 7.0, 6.9, rest of leg absent); III: - (5.8, rest of leg absent); IV: absent. Epigyne: EF roughly as wide as long; MAB short and narrow; MS tear-shaped, widest medially; EP triangular, longer than wide, opening slightly anterior to posterior margin of MS; LL touching posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFC3FFC51FC70FC36" box="[922,1022,987,1013]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–132" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1779,1803]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,181,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-23@38.[156,1430,181,1755]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 126–132. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 126–129 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (126 prolateral, 127 ventral, 128 retrolateral, 129 detail of embolus); 130–132 Female (AMNH, paratype) (130 epigyne, 131 vulva; 132 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection of the cymbium; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP— spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550486/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 130</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFBAFFC51FBB6FC35" box="[1034,1080,987,1014]" captionStart="FIGURES 133–137" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[260,1319,1226,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-521@39.[256,1332,1209,1940]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 133–137. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 133–135 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (133 prolateral, 134 ventral, 135 retrolateral); 136–137 Female (AMNH, paratype) (136 epigyne, 137 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550488/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">136</figureCitation>
). Vulva: internal ducts with FW not dilated, postero laterad; GP rounded, slightly longer than wide, arising from ducts at first turn; antero laterad; SP spherical; FD antero laterad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFE7BFBAAFDF2FBF8" box="[478,636,1056,1083]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–132" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1779,1803]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,181,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-23@38.[156,1430,181,1755]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 126–132. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 126–129 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (126 prolateral, 127 ventral, 128 retrolateral, 129 detail of embolus); 130–132 Female (AMNH, paratype) (130 epigyne, 131 vulva; 132 schematic course of internal duct system). ag—anterior groove; C—conductor; E—embolus; EP—epigynal pocket; ft—first turn of duct system; FD—fertilization duct; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MAB—muscle attachment bands; MS—median septum; PTA—prolateral tibial apophysis; RpP—retro proximal projection of the cymbium; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP— spermathecae. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550486/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figs 131–132</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFF84C92BFD22FBABFD3BFBF8" box="[647,693,1057,1083]" captionStart="FIGURES 133–137" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[260,1319,1226,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-521@39.[256,1332,1209,1940]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 133–137. Meri carabobo spec. nov. 133–135 Male (AMNH, holotype), left palp (133 prolateral, 134 ventral, 135 retrolateral); 136–137 Female (AMNH, paratype) (136 epigyne, 137 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550488" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550488/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">137</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
